The best approach for file system statics is the **`System.IO.Abstractions`** NuGet package — it's battle-tested and provides a drop-in `IFileSystem` abstraction. No need to write a custom wrapper.

Your `ReportGenerator.cs` also has other statics (`DateTime.UtcNow`, `Environment.*`, `Console.*`). Here's the full plan:

### 1. File System (`File.*`, `Directory.*`) → `System.IO.Abstractions`

```bash
dotnet add package System.IO.Abstractions
# For tests:
dotnet add <TestProject> package System.IO.Abstractions.TestingHelpers
```

Inject `IFileSystem` and use its members:

```csharp
public class ReportGenerator(IFileSystem fileSystem)
{
    // fileSystem.File.WriteAllText(path, content);
    // fileSystem.Directory.Exists(dir);
}
```

Test with `MockFileSystem`:

```csharp
var mockFs = new MockFileSystem();
var generator = new ReportGenerator(mockFs);
// mockFs now captures all file operations — assert against it
```

### 2. Time (`DateTime.UtcNow`) → `TimeProvider` (built-in on .NET 10)

```csharp
// DI registration:
builder.Services.AddSingleton(TimeProvider.System);

// Inject and use:
public class ReportGenerator(TimeProvider timeProvider)
{
    var now = timeProvider.GetUtcNow();
}

// Test with FakeTimeProvider (Microsoft.Extensions.TimeProvider.Testing NuGet)
```

### 3. Environment (`Environment.*`) → Custom `IEnvironmentProvider`

```csharp
public interface IEnvironmentProvider
{
    string? GetEnvironmentVariable(string variable);
    string MachineName { get; }
}

public sealed class EnvironmentProvider : IEnvironmentProvider
{
    public string? GetEnvironmentVariable(string variable)
        => Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable(variable);
    public string MachineName => Environment.MachineName;
}

// DI: builder.Services.AddSingleton<IEnvironmentProvider, EnvironmentProvider>();
```

### 4. Console (`Console.*`) → Custom `IConsole`

```csharp
public interface IConsole
{
    void WriteLine(string message);
}

public sealed class SystemConsole : IConsole
{
    public void WriteLine(string message) => Console.WriteLine(message);
}

// DI: builder.Services.AddSingleton<IConsole, SystemConsole>();
```

